                "invention-title": [
                    "Monatomic catalyst with low metal loading capacity and high exposure density as well as hydrogen bond assisted thermal activation preparation method, regeneration method and application of monatomic catalyst",
                    "一种低金属载量高暴露密度单原子催化剂及其氢键辅助热活化制备方法和再生方法及应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to the field of nano catalytic materials, in particular to a monatomic catalyst with low metal loading capacity and high exposure density as well as a hydrogen bond-assisted thermal activation preparation method, a regeneration method and application of the monatomic catalyst. According to the invention, a hydrogen bond-assisted synthesis strategy is utilized, a stable metal-nitrogen bonded substance is formed in the synthesis process of a monatomic precursor, and the bonded substance is fixed on the surface of a triazine ring molecule of carbon nitride, so that dispersion and anchoring of monatomic are effectively enhanced; in the thermal activation process, the longitudinal steric hindrance is enhanced through the surface of a thin nano layer sheet and a low-specific-surface-area carbon nitride carrier which are synthesized under the assistance of a hydrogen bond, longitudinal migration, agglomeration, embedding and the like of single atoms at high temperature are effectively avoided, meanwhile, the metal precursor is not cleaned before thermal activation, and the thermal activation time is shortened; finally, synthesis of the monatomic catalyst with ultrahigh monatomic exposure density is realized. According to the monatomic catalyst provided by the invention, the ultrahigh exposure density of more than 10 atoms nm &lt;-2 &gt; is achieved with the metal loading capacity of 6 wt.%."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及纳米催化材料领域，具体是一种低金属载量高暴露密度单原子催化剂及其氢键辅助热活化制备方法和再生方法及应用。本发明利用氢键辅助的合成策略，在单原子前体合成过程中形成了稳定的金属‑氮键合物，并将该键合物固定在氮化碳的三嗪环分子表面，有效地增强了单原子的分散与锚定；而热活化过程中，通过氢键辅助合成的薄纳米层片、低比表面积的氮化碳载体表面增强了纵向空间位阻，有效地避免了单原子在高温下的纵向迁移、团聚、包埋等，同时在热活化之前不对金属前驱体进行清洗，最终实现超高单原子暴露密度单原子催化剂的合成。本发明提供的单原子催化剂以6 wt.%金属负载量达到了10 atoms nm‑2以上的超高暴露密度。"
                }
            ]
        }
